    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>your Letter as usual obliges me much. I have read <hi rend="underline">some</hi>
                    of <persName ref="pe0156">Mr Lows</persName>
                    <sic>of</sic>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0058">Journal</title></bibl> &amp; am much
                    delighted with it. Pray lend him y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0020">new edition of Br.
                        Zool.</title></bibl> all the volumes; for I have no more to give away. They
                    will be of much use to him. He ought by all means to visit the northern
                        <placeName ref="pl0701">orknies</placeName> to complete his work. Which will
                    meet with encouragement. Pray write to him as much &amp; let him know I will
                    write soon.</p>
                <p>The libel is too low &amp; insignificant to <sic>to</sic> be attended to.<note type="editorial">See the postscript of Pennant's letter to Paton on 7
                        November 1777.</note></p>
                <closer><salute>adieu <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> affectly</salute>
                    <persName ref="pe0232">T Pennant.</persName>
                    <dateline>Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 30<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                        1774</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>inclosed is an order for <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora
                                Scotica</title></bibl></p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> George Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom house</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p><handShift/>came under cover to<persName ref="pe0022">D<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Ramsay</persName> who is confined to his room, &amp; wants to
                    see <persName ref="pe0228">M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Paton</persName>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
